title.narrative: BR Municipal APL: Teresina Enhancing Municipal Governance and Quality of Life Project

description.narrative: The objectives of the project are to (i) modernize and improve the management capacity of Teresina Municipal Government in the financial, urban, environmental, service-delivery, and economic development fields; and (ii) improve the quality of life of the low-income population of the Lagoas do Norte region of the city.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A, 1(a) - Implementation Arrangements - Institutional | Description :At all times duringexecution of the project, the Borrower shall maintain, until completion of the project a unit within SEMPLAN, to be responsible forthe overall coordination and implementation of the project (the "PMU"), such PMU to maintain staffing, functions andresponsibilities satisfactory to the Bank as set forth in the Operational Manual. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A, 1(b) - Implementation Arrangements, Institutional | Description :The Borrower shallmaintain until completion of the project a Project Steering Committee (or “PSC”), presided by the Borrower’s Mayor or itsdesignated representative, with the overall responsibility for providing policy oversight and guidance for the implementation ofthe Project and with powers and composition acceptable to the Bank as set forth in the Operational Manual. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, B - Implementation Arrangements - Operational Manual | Description :Without limitation tothe provisions of Section 5.01 of the General Conditions, the Borrower shall cause the Project to be carried out in accordance withthe provisions of a manual, satisfactory to the Bank (the “Operational Manual”), which shall detail the procedures and guidelinesfor the execution, monitoring and evaluation of the Project. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, D, 1 - Implementation Arrangements - Safeguards | Description :Without limitation to theprovisions of Section 5.01 (b) of the General Conditions, the Borrower shall carry out the Project in accordance with theprovisionsand recommendations of the Environmental Assessment, a respective ESMP, the Resettlement Policy Framework, the resultingResettlement Plans and the procedures outlined in the Operational Manual, when applicable. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, D, 2 - Implementation Arrangements - Safeguards | Description :Prior to initiatingbidding procedures for works, the Borrower shall, when applicable, submit to the Bank for its review and approval a ResettlementPlan for the population affected by the relevant works, to be prepared in accordance with the Resettlement Policy Framework. Priorto initiating works in selected Project areas, implement the Resettlement Plan in a manner satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency:CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, D, 3 - Implementation Arrangements - Safeguards | Description :The Borrower shall ensurethat any contractors that will carry out civil works under the Project shall perform their work in accordance with the technical,environmental and social practices for the Project, as set forth in the Environmental Assessment and respective ESMP. | Frequency:CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, D, 4 (a) - Implementation Arrangements - Safeguards | Description :The Borrower shallmaintain a dam safety panel with experts and terms of reference satisfactory to the Bank, which shall review the detailedengineering designs for works for the flood control dike along the Parnaíba river under Part 2(d) of the Project prior tocommencement of works. | Due Date :31-Dec-2018

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, D, 4 (b) - Implementation Arrangements - Safeguards | Description :The Borrower shallensure that contractors that will carry out said works shall follow the safety standards and recommendations of the dam safetypanel referred to in paragraph (a) above. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
